Class Panels.KWPriorityQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • Panels.KWPriorityQueue<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Queue<E>

    public class Panels.KWPriorityQueue<E>
extends java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
implements java.util.Queue<E>
    The Panels.KWPriorityQueue implements the Queue interface by building a heap in an ArrayList. The heap is structured so that the "smallest" item is at the top.
